page.title: 13ECOLOGY OF MOORSHOLM REGION
page.content: {FARMLAND} Supports lapwings, tawny owls, kestrels, yellow-hammers, magpies, jackdaws, rooks, jays, carrion crows, woodpigeons and linnets. {BROAD LEAVED WOODLAND} (Avens Wood, Gerrick Wood and along Hag Beck) The Nature Conservancy Council has designated part of this woodland as a site of Special Scientific Interest. This woodland supports dippers, green woodpeckers, cuckoos, coal and long-tailed tits, tree creepers, willow warblers and little owls. Red deer, foxes, rabbits, stoats, voles & moles also inhabit the woodland areas. {VILLAGE GARDENS} Frequently seen are blackbirds, hedge and house sparrows, starlings, robins, thrushes, pied-wagtails, blue and great tits, wrens, swallows, swifts, house martins, chaffinches and bramblings.
